    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Things Which Influence Us and Our Children</strong>&mdash;Every association we form, however limited, exerts some influence upon us. The extent to which we yield to that influence will be determined by the degree of intimacy, the constancy of the intercourse, and our love and veneration for the one with whom we associate.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">1<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"5T 222.1\" data-link=\"113.1142\">Testimonies for the Church 5:222, 223</span>.</span></a></sup>",
