    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The young, if brought under this influence, are more easily affected by it than those who are older. Everything leaves its impress upon their minds&mdash;the countenances they look upon, the voices they hear, the places they visit, the company they keep, and the books they read. It is impossible to overestimate the importance for this world and the next of the associations we choose for ourselves and, more especially, for our children.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">2<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"5T 543.1\" data-link=\"113.2659\">Ibid., 543</span>.</span></a></sup>",
