    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 460.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "It was by associating with idolaters and joining in their festivities that the Hebrews were led to transgress God&apos;s law and bring His judgments upon the nation. So now it is by leading the followers of Christ to associate with the ungodly and unite in their amusements that Satan is most successful in alluring them into sin. &ldquo;Come out from among them, and be ye separate, saith the Lord, and touch not the unclean.&rdquo; God requires of His people now as great a distinction from the world, in customs, habits, and principles, as He required of Israel anciently.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"PP 458.1\" data-link=\"84.2112\">Patriarchs and Prophets, 458</span>.</span></a></sup>",
