    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Many Yield to Temptation Through Fear of Ridicule</strong>&mdash;Children ... should have companions who will not ridicule what is pure and worthy, but will rather advocate what is right. The fear of ridicule leads many a youth to yield to temptation and to walk in the way of the ungodly. Mothers may do much by example as well as by precept to show their children how to be upright amid scorn and ridicule.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">13<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 3-31-1891\" data-link=\"821.11134\">The Review and Herald, March 31, 1891</span>.</span></a></sup>",
